**Clinical Reasoning:**
Metoprolol and verapamil both exert negative chronotropic and dromotropic effects by slowing conduction through the atrioventricular (AV) node. Combined use increases the likelihood of AV block, particularly in patients with preexisting conduction abnormalities. While mild bradycardia is common, combinations of these agents carry a documented risk of progressing to second-degree or even complete AV block, especially in vulnerable populations.

